{"title":"2026 Bespoked UK Selects 04: Auckland, Condor, No-Ni, Scolarian, Selwyn, Ted James, and Ten:07 – John Watson","link":"https://theradavist.com/2026-bespoked-uk-04","date":1777446008000,"content":"<p><em>John and Cari are at the <a href=\"https://theradavist.com/tag/2026-bespoked-uk\" target=\"_blank\">2026 Bespoked UK</a> show in London and are elated to share their third selection of bikes from the event with you, featuring <a href=\"https://theradavist.com/tag/auckland-cycle-works\" target=\"_blank\">Auckland</a>, <a href=\"https://theradavist.com/tag/condor-cycles\" target=\"_blank\">Condor</a>, <a href=\"https://theradavist.com/tag/no-ni-cycles\" target=\"_blank\">No-Ni</a>, <a href=\"https://theradavist.com/tag/posst-scolarian-works\" target=\"_blank\">Scolarian</a>, <a href=\"https://theradavist.com/tag/selwyn\" target=\"_blank\">Selwyn</a>, <a href=\"https://theradavist.com/tag/ted-james-design\" target=\"_blank\">Ted James</a>, and <a href=\"https://theradavist.com/tag/ten07\" target=\"_blank\">Ten:07</a>…</em><br />\n<span></span></p>\n<p><strong>The Radavist thanks <a href=\"https://www.brooksengland.com/\" target=\"_blank\">Brooks England</a> and <a href=\"https://www.schwalbe.com/\" target=\"_blank\">Schwalbe</a> for sponsoring our <a href=\"https://www.bespoked.cc/uk-2026\" target=\"_blank\">2026 Bespoked UK</a> coverage and our independent Reportage!</strong></p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Auckland-Cycle-Works-1.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Auckland-Cycle-Works-1.jpg?w=650&amp;quality=75 640w, https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Auckland-Cycle-Works-1.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75 1800w, https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Auckland-Cycle-Works-1.jpg?w=2000&amp;quality=75\" /></p>\n<h3><a href=\"https://www.aucklandcycle.works/pages/suspension/\" target=\"_blank\">Auckland Cycle Works Marra Full Suspension</a></h3>\n<p>Last year, I covered <a href=\"https://theradavist.com/2025-bespoked-uk-day-03#:~:text=Auckland%20Cycle%20Works%20Marra%20V2.3%20Full%20Suspension\" target=\"_blank\">Gary Ewing’s Marra 2.3 full suspension in Manchester</a>. This year, at the 2026 Bespoked UK showcase, Garry brought along the latest Marra frame, with a similar suspension layout but with a few key tweaks. In fact, this Marra has the same rear swingarm as the 2.3. All of the changes are on the front triangle.</p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Auckland-Cycle-Works-4.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Auckland-Cycle-Works-4.jpg?w=400&amp;quality=75 800w, https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Auckland-Cycle-Works-4.jpg?w=1000&amp;quality=75 1600w, https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Auckland-Cycle-Works-4.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75\" /><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Auckland-Cycle-Works-11.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Auckland-Cycle-Works-11.jpg?w=400&amp;quality=75 800w, https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Auckland-Cycle-Works-11.jpg?w=1000&amp;quality=75 1600w, https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Auckland-Cycle-Works-11.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75\" /></p>\n<p>For starters, the head tube gusset has changed into a sculptural element of the frame, which I quite liked. It feels more refined than the previous gusset.</p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Auckland-Cycle-Works-17.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Auckland-Cycle-Works-17.jpg?w=400&amp;quality=75 800w, https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Auckland-Cycle-Works-17.jpg?w=1000&amp;quality=75 1600w, https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Auckland-Cycle-Works-17.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75\" /><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Auckland-Cycle-Works-2.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Auckland-Cycle-Works-2.jpg?w=400&amp;quality=75 800w, https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Auckland-Cycle-Works-2.jpg?w=1000&amp;quality=75 1600w, https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Auckland-Cycle-Works-2.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75\" /></p>\n<p>Another key difference is the ability to adjust the top mount of the shock in 2 mm increments. To achieve this, Gary machined a steel insert that fits within the aluminum shock mount. This steel insert is notched, allowing for indexed shock locations. There are 16 notches on the top of this insert, 16 on the bottom, on both inserts – there are two, one for each side.</p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Auckland-Cycle-Works-18.jpg?w=600&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Auckland-Cycle-Works-18.jpg?w=300&amp;quality=75 800w, https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Auckland-Cycle-Works-18.jpg?w=600&amp;quality=75 1600w, https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Auckland-Cycle-Works-18.jpg?w=800&amp;quality=75\" /><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Auckland-Cycle-Works-19.jpg?w=600&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Auckland-Cycle-Works-19.jpg?w=300&amp;quality=75 800w, https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Auckland-Cycle-Works-19.jpg?w=600&amp;quality=75 1600w, https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Auckland-Cycle-Works-19.jpg?w=800&amp;quality=75\" /><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Auckland-Cycle-Works-29.jpg?w=600&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Auckland-Cycle-Works-29.jpg?w=300&amp;quality=75 800w, https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Auckland-Cycle-Works-29.jpg?w=600&amp;quality=75 1600w, https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Auckland-Cycle-Works-29.jpg?w=800&amp;quality=75\" /></p>\n<p>He also displayed some rather nice <a href=\"https://hexcomponents.com/\" target=\"_blank\">Hex Components</a> on this build, featuring a seat collar, headset cap, and bar end. Dang! Seeing them all together twisted my arm into spending some cash at the Hex booth.</p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Auckland-Cycle-Works-13.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Auckland-Cycle-Works-13.jpg?w=400&amp;quality=75 800w, https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Auckland-Cycle-Works-13.jpg?w=1000&amp;quality=75 1600w, https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Auckland-Cycle-Works-13.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75\" /><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Auckland-Cycle-Works-28.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Auckland-Cycle-Works-28.jpg?w=400&amp;quality=75 800w, https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Auckland-Cycle-Works-28.jpg?w=1000&amp;quality=75 1600w, https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Auckland-Cycle-Works-28.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75\" /></p>\n<p>Gary’s Auckland Cycle Works was named after the original 1890’s cycle factory in his hometown. Gary and his wife, Fiona, always bring the most refined examples of suspension kinematics to the Bespoked showcases. How good is that finish!</p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Auckland-Cycle-Works-26.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Auckland-Cycle-Works-26.jpg?w=650&amp;quality=75 640w, https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Auckland-Cycle-Works-26.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75 1800w, https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Auckland-Cycle-Works-26.jpg?w=2000&amp;quality=75\" /></p>\n<p>Check out <a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=9i_Wf5w4EA4\" target=\"_blank\">Auckland Cycle Works’ YouTube</a> for a nifty video showcasing suspension system animation using Legos, for us luddites who have a hard time with this sort of thing… ;-)</p>\n<h3><a href=\"https://www.instagram.com/aucklandcycleworks/\" target=\"_blank\">@AucklandCycleWorks</a></h3>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Condor-1.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Condor-1.jpg?w=650&amp;quality=75 640w, https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Condor-1.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75 1800w, https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Condor-1.jpg?w=2000&amp;quality=75\" /></p>\n<h3><a href=\"https://www.condorcycles.com/products/condor-italia-rc-ltd-frameset?_fid=780effad9&amp;_pos=3&amp;_ss=c&amp;variant=56042577396096\" target=\"_blank\">Condor Cycles</a> and <a href=\"https://portaromana.com/\" target=\"_blank\">Porta Romana</a> Gilded Bike</h3>\n<p>What began in 1948 as a framebuilding company in Islington, just outside of London, now has its frames made in Italy. Condor Cycles has a heritage of UK artistry, and so for this year’s show they teamed up with <a href=\"https://portaromana.com/\" target=\"_blank\">Porta Romana</a> on a special project. Porta Romana is a British lighting and furniture company renowned for their artisanal craftsmanship and hand-painted finishes, for a special edition of its Italia RC disc frame.</p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Condor-4.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Condor-4.jpg?w=650&amp;quality=75 640w, https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Condor-4.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75 1800w, https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Condor-4.jpg?w=2000&amp;quality=75\" /></p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Condor-24.jpg?w=600&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Condor-24.jpg?w=300&amp;quality=75 800w, https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Condor-24.jpg?w=600&amp;quality=75 1600w, https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Condor-24.jpg?w=800&amp;quality=75\" /><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Condor-23.jpg?w=600&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Condor-23.jpg?w=300&amp;quality=75 800w, https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Condor-23.jpg?w=600&amp;quality=75 1600w, https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Condor-23.jpg?w=800&amp;quality=75\" /><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Condor-31.jpg?w=600&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Condor-31.jpg?w=300&amp;quality=75 800w, https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Condor-31.jpg?w=600&amp;quality=75 1600w, https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Condor-31.jpg?w=800&amp;quality=75\" /></p>\n<p>At Porta Romana’s Surrey-based design studio, this Italia RC frameset underwent hours of meticulous preparation and finishing. The design team hand-applied a gilded finish to the Condor downtube logo, paired with their rich burnt ochre hand-painted finish. Every detail has been carefully considered, from brass headbadge to bottle cage bolts, resulting in a bicycle where performance engineering meets decorative artistry.</p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Condor-3.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Condor-3.jpg?w=650&amp;quality=75 640w, https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Condor-3.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75 1800w, https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Condor-3.jpg?w=2000&amp;quality=75\" /></p>\n<p>This stunning bike will be on display at Clerkenwell Design Week, where it will be raffled by Clerkenwheels. Their goal is to raise £10,000 for United in Design’s Education and Outreach Program, helping to transform the lives of 1,000 young people across the UK by improving access to the design industry for a more inclusive, representative design future.</p>\n<h3><a href=\"https://www.instagram.com/p/DXbuynxDC_6/\" target=\"_blank\">@CondorCycles</a></h3>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-No-Ni-1.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-No-Ni-1.jpg?w=650&amp;quality=75 640w, https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-No-Ni-1.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75 1800w, https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-No-Ni-1.jpg?w=2000&amp;quality=75\" /></p>\n<h3><a href=\"https://www.instagram.com/noni_cycles/\" target=\"_blank\">No-Ni Stainless and Carbon Gravel</a></h3>\n<p>Glasgow, Scotland-based No-Ni is a small framebuilding operation from Kevin Pollock, a career furniture and industrial designer. Last year I documented <a href=\"https://theradavist.com/2025-bespoked-uk-day-03#:~:text=No%2DNi%20Cycles%20Stainless%20Gravel%20Touring%20Bike\" target=\"_blank\">his first Bespoked UK offerings</a>, and this year he returned to the 2026 Bespoked UK with a stunning stainless steel and carbon fiber gravel road bike. Kevin stated that his inspiration for the project was the Ritte Muur frame.</p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-No-Ni-13.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-No-Ni-13.jpg?w=400&amp;quality=75 800w, https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-No-Ni-13.jpg?w=1000&amp;quality=75 1600w, https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-No-Ni-13.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75\" /><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-No-Ni-17.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-No-Ni-17.jpg?w=400&amp;quality=75 800w, https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-No-Ni-17.jpg?w=1000&amp;quality=75 1600w, https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-No-Ni-17.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75\" /></p>\n<p>Thanks to the new 3D printed chainstay yoke and drop stay design, the new bike fits a 29 x 2.3″ tire. This 50 mm Schwalbe G-One RX has heaps of room in the rear end.</p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-No-Ni-37.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-No-Ni-37.jpg?w=400&amp;quality=75 800w, https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-No-Ni-37.jpg?w=1000&amp;quality=75 1600w, https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-No-Ni-37.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75\" /><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-No-Ni-36.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-No-Ni-36.jpg?w=400&amp;quality=75 800w, https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-No-Ni-36.jpg?w=1000&amp;quality=75 1600w, https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-No-Ni-36.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75\" /></p>\n<p>When I asked Kevin Pollock what prompted this new carbon fiber direction, he stated, “The thing I’ve been working on the most since the last Bespoked is the rear. Been trying to tune the ride feel.” He found the best way to fine-tune ride feel was to experiment with carbon layups. Kevin used to work primarily in product design and extensively with carbon. “I did a load of carbon layup stuff in product design departments.”</p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-No-Ni-22.jpg?w=600&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-No-Ni-22.jpg?w=300&amp;quality=75 800w, https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-No-Ni-22.jpg?w=600&amp;quality=75 1600w, https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-No-Ni-22.jpg?w=800&amp;quality=75\" /><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-No-Ni-27.jpg?w=600&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-No-Ni-27.jpg?w=300&amp;quality=75 800w, https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-No-Ni-27.jpg?w=600&amp;quality=75 1600w, https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-No-Ni-27.jpg?w=800&amp;quality=75\" /><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-No-Ni-31.jpg?w=600&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-No-Ni-31.jpg?w=300&amp;quality=75 800w, https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-No-Ni-31.jpg?w=600&amp;quality=75 1600w, https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-No-Ni-31.jpg?w=800&amp;quality=75\" /></p>\n<p>This is evident in his obsession with making his stainless lugs lay flush with the carbon tubing, achieved by sleeving the two frame parts together. The internal dimension was more critical, so he made the mandrels for the carbon layup to reflect this flush finish.</p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-No-Ni-40.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-No-Ni-40.jpg?w=650&amp;quality=75 640w, https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-No-Ni-40.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75 1800w, https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-No-Ni-40.jpg?w=2000&amp;quality=75\" /></p>\n<p>No-Ni brings a vibe to Bespoked. It feels more California than Scotland, but perhaps that’s just Kevin’s aura.</p>\n<p>Peace, dude!</p>\n<h3><a href=\"https://www.instagram.com/noni_cycles/\" target=\"_blank\">@No-NiCycles</a></h3>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Scolarian-1.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Scolarian-1.jpg?w=650&amp;quality=75 640w, https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Scolarian-1.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75 1800w, https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Scolarian-1.jpg?w=2000&amp;quality=75\" /></p>\n<h3><a href=\"https://www.scolarian.com/\" target=\"_blank\">Scolarian Fixed Freestyle</a></h3>\n<p>What is this, 2008? Have we gone full circle? I believe so. <a href=\"https://www.instagram.com/robinditchburn/\" target=\"_blank\">Robin Ditchburn</a> contacted India’s Scolarian to build him a custom fixed freestyle bike for curb jibs and wheelies all around London.</p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Scolarian-7.jpg?w=600&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Scolarian-7.jpg?w=300&amp;quality=75 800w, https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Scolarian-7.jpg?w=600&amp;quality=75 1600w, https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Scolarian-7.jpg?w=800&amp;quality=75\" /><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Scolarian-29.jpg?w=600&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Scolarian-29.jpg?w=300&amp;quality=75 800w, https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Scolarian-29.jpg?w=600&amp;quality=75 1600w, https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Scolarian-29.jpg?w=800&amp;quality=75\" /><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Scolarian-14.jpg?w=600&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Scolarian-14.jpg?w=300&amp;quality=75 800w, https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Scolarian-14.jpg?w=600&amp;quality=75 1600w, https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Scolarian-14.jpg?w=800&amp;quality=75\" /></p>\n<p>And boy did they deliver. Robin has had the bike for six months already and has been riding it extensively after building it up a short while ago. For him, the bike achieved everything he wanted for a real urban bruiser.</p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Scolarian-28.jpg?w=600&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Scolarian-28.jpg?w=300&amp;quality=75 800w, https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Scolarian-28.jpg?w=600&amp;quality=75 1600w, https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Scolarian-28.jpg?w=800&amp;quality=75\" /><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Scolarian-25.jpg?w=600&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Scolarian-25.jpg?w=300&amp;quality=75 800w, https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Scolarian-25.jpg?w=600&amp;quality=75 1600w, https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Scolarian-25.jpg?w=800&amp;quality=75\" /><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Scolarian-26.jpg?w=600&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Scolarian-26.jpg?w=300&amp;quality=75 800w, https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Scolarian-26.jpg?w=600&amp;quality=75 1600w, https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Scolarian-26.jpg?w=800&amp;quality=75\" /></p>\n<p>The geometry was designed around an Identiti dirt jumper fork, which clears a 700c wheel. He’s using Bits By Be straps, Brick Lane Bikes hubs, Omnium cranks (what a throwback), and various details made by Hex Components.</p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Scolarian-2.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Scolarian-2.jpg?w=650&amp;quality=75 640w, https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Scolarian-2.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75 1800w, https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Scolarian-2.jpg?w=2000&amp;quality=75\" /></p>\n<p>If you have a custom bike dream, holler at Scolarian! And if you’re in London, holler at Robin. He can facilitate working with the brand in India.</p>\n<h3><a href=\"https://www.instagram.com/scolarian_bikes/\" target=\"_blank\">@ScolarianBikes</a></h3>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Selwyn-1.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Selwyn-1.jpg?w=650&amp;quality=75 640w, https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Selwyn-1.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75 1800w, https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Selwyn-1.jpg?w=2000&amp;quality=75\" /></p>\n<h3><a href=\"https://selwynbicycles.com/fullsuspension\" target=\"_blank\">Selwyn Bicycles 160/140 Trail Bike</a></h3>\n<p>Alexander Plaisted came out of the Bicycle Academy in London and now lives in the French Alps where he builds bikes under Selwyn Bicycles. For the 2026 Bespoked UK show in London, he brought the latest model of his 160/140 mm trail bike.</p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Selwyn-5.jpg?w=600&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Selwyn-5.jpg?w=300&amp;quality=75 800w, https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Selwyn-5.jpg?w=600&amp;quality=75 1600w, https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Selwyn-5.jpg?w=800&amp;quality=75\" /><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Selwyn-9.jpg?w=600&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Selwyn-9.jpg?w=300&amp;quality=75 800w, https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Selwyn-9.jpg?w=600&amp;quality=75 1600w, https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Selwyn-9.jpg?w=800&amp;quality=75\" /><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Selwyn-39.jpg?w=600&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Selwyn-39.jpg?w=300&amp;quality=75 800w, https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Selwyn-39.jpg?w=600&amp;quality=75 1600w, https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Selwyn-39.jpg?w=800&amp;quality=75\" /></p>\n<p>He utilizes 3D printed stainless steel parts for the dropouts, chainstay yoke, and seatstay clevices, which he then silver solders to the stainless tubing for the seat stays and 853 for the chainstays. The front triangle uses Reynolds 853 and 931 tubing. Alex has developed a system at the silver anodized 7075 aluminum rocker links to elimitate twisting at the connection.</p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Selwyn-22.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Selwyn-22.jpg?w=400&amp;quality=75 800w, https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Selwyn-22.jpg?w=1000&amp;quality=75 1600w, https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Selwyn-22.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75\" /><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Selwyn-4.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Selwyn-4.jpg?w=400&amp;quality=75 800w, https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Selwyn-4.jpg?w=1000&amp;quality=75 1600w, https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Selwyn-4.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75\" /></p>\n<p>The rest of the front end is fillet brazed together, delivering a package that is as sturdy as it is sexy. I love the cable routing on these bikes and how the seatstay pops against the black backdrop.</p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Selwyn-35.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Selwyn-35.jpg?w=650&amp;quality=75 640w, https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Selwyn-35.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75 1800w, https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Selwyn-35.jpg?w=2000&amp;quality=75\" /></p>\n<p>New for 2026 is Selwyn’s partnership with the French shock company Fast, who makes a tune that’s unique to the Selwyn kinematics to ensure you get the most traction and support from your ride.</p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Selwyn-34.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Selwyn-34.jpg?w=650&amp;quality=75 640w, https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Selwyn-34.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75 1800w, https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Selwyn-34.jpg?w=2000&amp;quality=75\" /></p>\n<p>If you’re interested in ordering a Selwyn, Alex works with MTB tours in the French Alps and can coordinate hotel bookings and rides for you after you pick up your new bike! Not a bad way to get your new MTB dirty, huh?</p>\n<h3><a href=\"https://www.instagram.com/selwynbicycles/\" target=\"_blank\">@SelwynBicycles</a></h3>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Ted-James-Design-1.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Ted-James-Design-1.jpg?w=650&amp;quality=75 640w, https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Ted-James-Design-1.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75 1800w, https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Ted-James-Design-1.jpg?w=2000&amp;quality=75\" /></p>\n<h3><a href=\"https://tedjamesdesign.com/\" target=\"_blank\">Ted James Design Mid Pivot Gearbox Titanium Full Suspension</a></h3>\n<p>If the Bespoked UK showcase is an opportunity to document project progression like this, I’m all for it. Last year, Ted James of Ted James Design debuted his <a href=\"https://theradavist.com/2025-bespoked-uk-day-02#:~:text=Ted%20James%20Design%20Prototype%20Full%20Suspension\" target=\"_blank\">monster of a gearbox steel full suspension</a>. He finished last year’s bike in the wee hours of the morning of the show. This year he rolled out a beastly, yet more refined, titanium version.</p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Ted-James-Design-27.jpg?w=600&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Ted-James-Design-27.jpg?w=300&amp;quality=75 800w, https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Ted-James-Design-27.jpg?w=600&amp;quality=75 1600w, https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Ted-James-Design-27.jpg?w=800&amp;quality=75\" /><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Ted-James-Design-18.jpg?w=600&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Ted-James-Design-18.jpg?w=300&amp;quality=75 800w, https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Ted-James-Design-18.jpg?w=600&amp;quality=75 1600w, https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Ted-James-Design-18.jpg?w=800&amp;quality=75\" /><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Ted-James-Design-25.jpg?w=600&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Ted-James-Design-25.jpg?w=300&amp;quality=75 800w, https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Ted-James-Design-25.jpg?w=600&amp;quality=75 1600w, https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Ted-James-Design-25.jpg?w=800&amp;quality=75\" /></p>\n<p>I greatly appreciate Ted’s pushing of the paradigm when it comes to bikes like this, where he machines literally every part he can, including the lockrings for the Gates cogs, which he used a dividing head manual mill to achieve the notching.</p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Ted-James-Design-20.jpg?w=600&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Ted-James-Design-20.jpg?w=300&amp;quality=75 800w, https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Ted-James-Design-20.jpg?w=600&amp;quality=75 1600w, https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Ted-James-Design-20.jpg?w=800&amp;quality=75\" /><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Ted-James-Design-21.jpg?w=600&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Ted-James-Design-21.jpg?w=300&amp;quality=75 800w, https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Ted-James-Design-21.jpg?w=600&amp;quality=75 1600w, https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Ted-James-Design-21.jpg?w=800&amp;quality=75\" /><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Ted-James-Design-22.jpg?w=600&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Ted-James-Design-22.jpg?w=300&amp;quality=75 800w, https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Ted-James-Design-22.jpg?w=600&amp;quality=75 1600w, https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Ted-James-Design-22.jpg?w=800&amp;quality=75\" /></p>\n<p>His attention to detail doesn’t stop at the kinematics, though. He made his own head tube cups, sleeving the lower bearing cup into the head tube to strengthen it, then anodized purple flames at the head tube cluster, and finished it all off with one of his head badges. This was a custom build for a client who primarily rides bike parks with it, and thus experiences a fair amount of thrashin’ and crashin’, so Ted used appropriate wall thickness tubing to ensure the client’s safety.</p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Ted-James-Design-17.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Ted-James-Design-17.jpg?w=400&amp;quality=75 800w, https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Ted-James-Design-17.jpg?w=1000&amp;quality=75 1600w, https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Ted-James-Design-17.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75\" /><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Showcase-81-1.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Showcase-81-1.jpg?w=400&amp;quality=75 800w, https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Showcase-81-1.jpg?w=1000&amp;quality=75 1600w, https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Showcase-81-1.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75\" /></p>\n<p>The following day, I managed to snag a nice portrait of Ted with a surfboard he made. Always good to see you, Ted! I can’t wait to see what you cook up for next year.</p>\n<h3><a href=\"https://www.instagram.com/tedjamesdesign/\" target=\"_blank\">@TedJamesDesign</a></h3>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Ten07-1.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Ten07-1.jpg?w=650&amp;quality=75 640w, https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Ten07-1.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75 1800w, https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Ten07-1.jpg?w=2000&amp;quality=75\" /></p>\n<h3><a href=\"https://ten07.cc/products/unicorn-pony-mini-cargo\" target=\"_blank\">Ten:07 Unicorn Pony Mini Velo Cargo Bike</a></h3>\n<p>After the success of its Unicorn Cargo Bike, Haarlem, Netherlands-based cargo brand Ten:07 unveiled its Unicorn Pony Mini Velo Cargo Bike at the 2026 Bespoked UK showcase. Designed for maximum cargo and minimum footprint in a home or apartment, the Unicorn Pony is designed for riders between 1.5 and 2.0 meters tall.</p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Ten07-6.jpg?w=600&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Ten07-6.jpg?w=300&amp;quality=75 800w, https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Ten07-6.jpg?w=600&amp;quality=75 1600w, https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Ten07-6.jpg?w=800&amp;quality=75\" /><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Ten07-9.jpg?w=600&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Ten07-9.jpg?w=300&amp;quality=75 800w, https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Ten07-9.jpg?w=600&amp;quality=75 1600w, https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Ten07-9.jpg?w=800&amp;quality=75\" /><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Ten07-5.jpg?w=600&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Ten07-5.jpg?w=300&amp;quality=75 800w, https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Ten07-5.jpg?w=600&amp;quality=75 1600w, https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Ten07-5.jpg?w=800&amp;quality=75\" /></p>\n<p>It utilizes a Gates drive with Rohloff hub and has internal dropper post routing, dynamo routing, a kickstand mount, fender mounts, and rack mounts. It also fits a 70 mm tire. The frame kit includes a frame, fork, rack platform, seatpost collar, and thru-axles, with a €999 retail or €2,249 for a complete build kit, similar to what is shown here.</p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Ten07-21.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Ten07-21.jpg?w=650&amp;quality=75 640w, https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Ten07-21.jpg?w=1400&amp;quality=75 1800w, https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/2026-Bespoked-UK-Ten07-21.jpg?w=2000&amp;quality=75\" /></p>\n<p>Ten:07 has pre-orders open now and is expecting the frame late July/early August. See more at <a href=\"https://ten07.cc/products/unicorn-pony-mini-cargo\" target=\"_blank\">Ten:07</a>.</p>\n<h3><a href=\"https://www.instagram.com/ten07.cc/\" target=\"_blank\">@Ten07</a></h3>\n<p><em><strong>Yep… We’ve got even more on the way from the 2026 Bespoked UK in London!</strong></em></p>\n<p><em><strong>Which build was your favorite? We’ve got a lot more on the way, so stay tuned…</strong></em></p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/CoverageSponsoredby_Schwalbe_Brooks.png?w=1400&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/CoverageSponsoredby_Schwalbe_Brooks.png?w=650&amp;quality=75 640w, https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/CoverageSponsoredby_Schwalbe_Brooks.png?w=1400&amp;quality=75 1800w, https://images.theradavist.com/uploads/2026/04/CoverageSponsoredby_Schwalbe_Brooks.png?w=2000&amp;quality=75\" /></p>\n<p><strong>The Radavist thanks <a href=\"https://www.brooksengland.com/\" target=\"_blank\">Brooks England</a> and <a href=\"https://www.schwalbe.com/\" target=\"_blank\">Schwalbe</a> for sponsoring our 2026 Bespoked UK coverage and our independent Reportage!</strong></p>\n<p> </p>\n<h3>All of our 2026 Bespoked UK photos are in <a href=\"https://www.dropbox.com/scl/fo/ub22h6il3xptz4rylnp42/AEloQInROxd7SbFXSmyuPWw?rlkey=l5crjp8imc8scm6ufw7a478ug&amp;st=igwozq3p&amp;dl=0\" target=\"_blank\">The Radavist Dropbox</a> for builders to use.</h3>\n<p>The post <a href=\"https://theradavist.com/2026-bespoked-uk-04\">2026 Bespoked UK Selects 04: Auckland, Condor, No-Ni, Scolarian, Selwyn, Ted James, and Ten:07</a> appeared first on <a href=\"https://cms.theradavist.com\">The Radavist</a>.</p>","author":"John Watson","siteTitle":"The Radavist","siteHash":"96eb481d8084f04a4602bac57874ba717baf56b758f45547b5caf2312da766ef","entryHash":"2562525d82efb2b4a782ec8cfffbe2c23d2340be745ecf7d4e64faaa52f18590","category":"Cycling"}